💫 ARE YOU ITCHING TO BRING YOUR IDEAS TO LIFE? 💫

UDesign is here to help! With a team of star-quality designers and affordable rates, we pride ourselves in the professional quality of our client-facing works, ranging from creative to product design! 🎯 🏆

To apply, we only need to hear about your:
🌟 Initial project goals and vision
🌟 Desired timeline and budget
🌟 Or any other inspirations that you have up your sleeves!

So send us your beautiful, still-brewing ideas!

⏰ Time? No need to worry—our application process is ongoing during the 2024-2025 school year!  
🔗 Ready to send us your ideas? Then check out the link in our bio and submit the form to udesigntoronto@gmail.com with the email subject titled, ‘Project Application’!

Triple En-Genre Presents: The Friday the 13th Horror Movie Special!

Hot off a SOLD OUT show last week, Triple En-Genre has assembled one of the most stacked casts in its show history for a special night of improvised thrills, chills, and scares (and laughter, of course).

Come see our talented cast of genre specialists improvise a Summer Camp Slasher, a Paranormal Horror, a Trapped Horror, and an Alien Horror movie.

Featuring:

Opening the show we have some special guests from UCB LA: Anna Bezahler and Isabella Escalante! They’ll be joined by Shainu Bala, Lance Oribello and Amanda Myers in the Paranormal Horror set.

Up second the scarily talented J.J. Greenberg, Sinthea Chowdhury, Phil Johnston, Niamh Lynch, Charles Nichols and Glenna Walters will be improvising a Trapped Horror movie.

In the third set, the improvised Alien Horror set, the eerily talented Nitin Anand, Aditya Chugh, Jeff Fernandes, Belle Gillis, Sam Needham and Meryem Sena will be fighting off extraterrestrial threats.

And finally, closing the show will be Tim Blair, Emma Decorte, Sachin Sinha, and Josh Zimmerman. In true Friday the 13th style, they’ll be improvising a Summer Camp Slasher.

Tickets at engenre.eventbrite.ca or at the link in bio.

🔈 THE WAIT IS OVER! 🔈

HSM’s choir practices are starting this week, with our first one happening tomorrow, Tuesday, September 17, from 2-3pm in Room 109 of the Edward Johnson Building!

Moving forward, choir practice meetings will be happening at the same building every:
